  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare two novel active rewarming techniques in mildly
      hypothermic people. Volunteers will undergo 3 cooling trials in a circulating bath at 14
      degrees celsius and will then be rewarmed with either shivering alone, warmed iv fluids
      (IVF), or water perfusion pads applied to the hands and feet. The investigators hypothesize
      that both heated IVF and water perfusion pads to the arteriovenous anastomoses (AVAs) will
      prove to provide significantly superior rewarming rates than shivering alone.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
